  Key Points to Say in Interview
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  ▎ "I track occupancy as a Set[str] of spot IDs in ParkingLot, not as a flag on ParkingSpot. Occupancy is relational state — a ticket-to-spot assignment managed by the orchestrator — not an intrinsic 
  property of the spot itself. The set gives O(1) lookup in _find_available_spot.                                                                                                                               
  
  ▎ For concurrency, I lock the entire enter method. The race window is between find_available_spot and _occupied_spot_ids.add — if two threads interleave there, both get the same spot. The lock makes        
  check-and-assign atomic. For a 3-5 entrance lot, serializing enter is correct and the throughput is fine.
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  ▎ exit also locks: it reads the ticket, computes the fee, frees the spot, and deletes the ticket atomically. Deleting the ticket is what prevents double-exit — the second call finds get() returning None.   
  
  ▎ Ticket is frozen because it's a receipt — immutable by definition. _compute_fee uses math.ceil for the round-up rule, with a minimum of 1 hour."  
